# 🔒 Security

## Project Isolation

Every query, job, and stored artifact must be scoped by `project_id`. Retrieval queries must always include the Project (and any required metadata) as filters; providers translate these into vendor-specific syntax. No cross-Project data access is permitted.

---

## Prompt Injection Defense

Never allow user input to override system prompts.

---

## Validation

Validate:

* Inputs
* Outputs
* JSON Structure
* Toxic Content

---

## RBAC

Protect:

* Prompt Editing
* Reindexing
* Administrative Actions

---

## Secret Management

Never commit API keys.

Use environment variables.

---

## PII Redaction

Detect and mask PII during:

* Ingestion
* Context Building

---

## Audit Logging

Log:

* Model Changes
* Prompt Updates
* Document Deletion
* Exports
* Evaluations

---

## Rate Limiting

Apply limits by:

* User
* Project
* API Key

---

# 🏭 Production & Enterprise Standards

## API Versioning

All public routes are versioned under `/api/v1/...`. Breaking changes require a new version, never a silent change to an existing one.

---

## API reference documentation (`docs/api/`)

Maintain a **module-grouped API collection** under `docs/api/` — concise reference
for Postman import, not tutorials.

* `docs/api/README.md` — base URL, response envelope, module index
* One file per module: `docs/api/projects.md`, `docs/api/knowledge.md`, …
* Per endpoint: method, path, one-line purpose, sample request/response JSON
* Update when routes ship or change; OpenAPI (`/docs`) remains the live contract

---

## Database Migrations

All schema changes go through Alembic migrations. Never auto-create or mutate tables at runtime in production.

---

## Standard Error Model

Errors return a consistent envelope: `code`, `message`, `trace_id`, and optional `details`. No raw stack traces leak to clients.

---

## Idempotency

Ingestion and job submission must be idempotent via idempotency keys or content hashes, so retries never cause duplicate processing.

---

## Health & Readiness

Expose:

* `/health` — liveness
* `/ready` — dependency checks (PostgreSQL, Redis, Vector DB, providers)

---

## Data Deletion

Deleting a Project or Document cascades across PostgreSQL, the Vector Store, and Object Storage to support right-to-be-forgotten.

Cross-module delete: the knowledge delete path invokes `RetrievalCleanupService`
(composition layer) to purge `chunk_embeddings` rows and best-effort vector points
without wiring the full embedding/indexing stack into knowledge DI.

---

## Configuration Precedence

Resolution order:

```
defaults → environment → database → per-Project overrides
```

---

## Testing

* Unit-test services with faked providers and repositories.
* Contract-test each provider against its abstract interface.
* Integration-test full pipelines end-to-end.

---

## Containerization

Ship as Docker images. Provide a docker-compose stack for the full self-hosted deployment (API, worker, PostgreSQL, Qdrant, Redis, object storage).

---

# 📦 Module Architecture (Canonical)

APE is a **modular monolith**. The canonical layout supersedes any earlier
description of global `services/`, `repositories/`, or `providers/` packages at
the application root.

```text
backend/app/
├── composition/    # ORM registry for Alembic (imports app.models)
├── models/         # All SQLAlchemy ORM entities (shared across modules)
├── api/            # HTTP composition (mount routers)
│   └── v1/routes/  # Per-feature routers + Depends() wiring
├── dependencies/   # FastAPI DI factories (composition only)
├── core/           # Cross-cutting (config, logging, exceptions)
├── platform/       # Shared kernel (db, infra, persistence, jobs, http)
└── modules/        # Feature vertical slices (no HTTP wiring, no ORM models)
```

**Full specification:** `docs/architecture/module-architecture.md`

## Module internal structure

```text
modules/<feature>/
    services/       # Business orchestration + transaction control
    repositories/   # AsyncRepository or ProjectScopedRepository subclasses
    schemas/        # Module-specific Pydantic request/response models
    workflows/      # Optional — complex pipelines only
```

ORM models belong in `app/models/`, not inside modules. HTTP routes live in
`api/v1/routes/`, not inside modules.

## Dependency rules

| Package | May import | Forbidden |
| ------- | ---------- | --------- |
| `core/` | stdlib, third-party | `platform`, `modules`, `models`, `api`, `dependencies`, `composition` |
| `platform/` | `core` | `modules`, `models`, `api`, `dependencies`, `composition` |
| `modules/<A>/` | `core`, `platform`, `app.models`, own package | `dependencies`, `api`, `composition`, `modules/<B>/` internals |
| `api/`, `dependencies/` | `core`, `platform`, `modules`, `app.models` | business logic |
| `composition/` | anywhere needed for ORM registry | — |

Enforced by `tests/architecture/test_import_boundaries.py`.

## Planned modules (bounded contexts)

```text
modules/projects/ modules/knowledge/ modules/retrieval/
modules/conversations/ modules/evaluation/
```

Provider **implementations** live in `platform/providers/implementations/`, not
inside feature modules.

---

# 🚫 Forbidden Practices

## ❌ Unscoped Data Access

Never read or write data without a `project_id` scope.

---

## ❌ Vendor Lock-in

Never call vendor SDKs directly from services.

---

## ❌ SDK Leakage

Never expose vendor models outside providers.

---

## ❌ Blocking AI Calls

Never execute OCR or embedding generation inside HTTP requests.

---

## ❌ Prompt Spaghetti

Never embed prompts directly inside business logic.

---

## ❌ Vector-only Retrieval (production RAG)

Production RAG paths (e.g. Chat) must use hybrid retrieval (BM25 + vector + RRF +
reranker). Phase 1 ships a **semantic baseline** only (ADR-007); do not treat it
as the final production search path.

---

## ❌ No Retry Policies

Every provider should support retries and graceful fallback.

---

## ❌ Silent Exceptions

Never swallow exceptions.

Always:

* Log Traceback
* Attach Trace ID
* Return Meaningful Errors
